6. Functional Requirements

FR-001 Environment Configuration

Framework shall load environment-specific configuration independent of inventory host definitions.

FR-002 Runtime Host Selection

Framework shall accept target host at execution time.

FR-003 Manifest Validation

Framework shall validate user-provided execution manifests.

FR-004 Artifact Deployment

Framework shall deploy artifacts from configured repositories.

FR-005 Artifact Execution

Framework shall execute artifact-specific commands.

FR-006 Parallel Execution

Framework shall support execution of multiple artifacts concurrently.

Maximum parallel artifacts:

5

FR-007 Sequential Execution

Framework shall support ordered execution of artifacts.

FR-008 Validation

Framework shall compare actual outputs against expected outputs.

FR-009 Reporting

Framework shall generate:

- Artifact reports
- Validation reports
- Execution summaries

FR-010 Notifications

Framework shall support:

- Failure notifications
- Completion notifications
- Summary notifications

FR-011 Resume

Framework shall support artifact-boundary resume execution.

